events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 32 points and nine assists as the Detroit Pistons reached .500 for the first time after New Year's Day since 2019 with a 118-115 win over the Portland Trail Blazers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cade Cunningham leads Pistons' rally for 118-115 win over Blazers and rare .500 record

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal came off the bench for the first time in nine years and scored 25 points as the Phoenix Suns ended a four-game skid with a 109-99 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bradley Beal comes off the bench to score 25 as Suns top 76ers 109-99 to end 4-game skid

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 23 points, Bennedict Mathurin added 20 and the Indiana Pacers beat the Brooklyn Nets 113-99 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton scores 23 points to help Pacers beat Nets 113-99

events.name: Orlando Magic at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony scored 24 points, Wendell Carter Jr. had a season-high 19 off the bench and the Orlando Magic shut down a New York Knicks team missing Karl-Anthony Towns for a 103-94 victory on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic hand Knicks season-high third straight loss with 103-94 victory

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 11 points, 13 assists and 12 rebounds for his fourth triple-double of the season, Damian Lillard scored 25 points and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the struggling Toronto Raptors 128-104 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo's triple-double, Lillard's 25 points power Bucks past struggling Raptors 128-104

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Coby White made a go-ahead layup with 47 seconds left, and the Chicago Bulls topped Victor Wembanyama and the San Antonio Spurs 114-110 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White stars as Bulls rally past Spurs for 114-110 victory

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 35 points, 13 rebounds and five assists to lead the Memphis Grizzlies to a 119-104 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaren Jackson Jr. scores 35 points to lead Grizzlies past Mavs 119-104

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 28 of his 37 points in the second half and the Minnesota Timberwolves overcame a 19-point first-half deficit to beat the Los Angeles Clippers 108-106 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 37 to lead Timberwolves past Clippers 108-106

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored nine of Sacramento’s 11 points in the second overtime, and the Kings beat the Miami Heat 123-118 on Monday night to extend their winning streak to a season-high five games under interim coach Doug Christie.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan shines as Kings hold off Heat 123-118 in double overtime
